OL,3,CPrison officer cries as secret
OL,4,Cmessages to inmate exposed
OL,6,FThe court heard there is no evidence
OL,7,Fto say she provided the illicit phone
OL,8,Fto the prisoner, and that the
OL,9,Funauthorised phone was never
OL,10,Fdiscovered.
OL,12,FDefence counsel Kimberley Obrusik told
OL,13,Fthe court Turner had been manipulated
OL,14,Fby a 'sophisticated criminal' and
OL,15,Ffeared she could be blackmailed.
OL,17,FShe said the mum-of-one had since
OL,18,Fresigned from the prison service and
OL,19,Ffound new employment.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
